CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 6, 1948, pg. 1, reads: "Victory Workers - Democratic workers in Hill District were busy all day Tuesday helping to get out the record vote which spelled victory for President Truman and the party. Left to right, are: Lieut. James Robertson, Voyle Parker, city detective; Mrs. Eliza Robertson, mother of the lieutenant, and Houston Calloway. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Lieut. James Robertson, Voyle Parker, Eliza Robertson, and Houston Calloway standing in front of Iron City Elks building with posters inscribed "Teamsters for Truman," and "Vote Against Taft-Hartley Law"
